    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Additive color system devised by chemist Wilhelm Ostwald; based on 24 foundation colors arranged in a disc; each then have white and black added to form tints or shades; used predominantly in the mid-twentieth century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
